Job Brief

Environment & Health Data Scientist, Lead Poisoning Prevention Program (India)

Vital Strategies India Services Private Limited, with a registered office in New Delhi, is a social enterprise that provides technical and management consultancy services to address the leading causes of death, disease, or injury and improve health outcomes. It seeks to provide innovative, cost-efficient solutions to global clients that are locally relevant, effective, and enduring by pursuing high-value partnerships and leveraging India s high-quality human capital and technology advantage.

Lead Poisoning Prevention Program

Vital Strategies is expanding our program that addresses the issue of lead poisoning in low- and middle-income countries. We plan to build upon existing efforts and interest by collaborating with governmental agencies in countries in Africa, Asia, and Latin America to strengthen health systems and build local expertise in childhood lead exposure to enact sound, cost-effective policies to address exposures.

Job Purpose

The Environment and Health Data Scientist, Lead Poisoning Prevention Program, will serve as the data science specialist supporting the development of integrated data systems to inform public health planning and policy in countries in Asia, Latin America, and Africa. This position will develop tools and guidance and support country teams to develop data platforms that integrate information on health, the environment, and populations to understand lead exposure risk. This position will be responsible for developing toolkits and facilitating local adaptation of these tools to identify the proper host for the data platform, inventory relevant data sources, manage and align datasets, analyze, visualize, and automate datasets, provide support for the selection and oversight of local data systems contractors and consultants, and support data integration efforts across systems. Beyond technical work, the role will work closely with global teams and governments to facilitate data sharing and integration.

This role will be based in the US, on a full-time hybrid schedule, out of Vital Strategies office in New York City. We are also open to qualified candidates from Ethiopia and India. Vital Strategies offers highly competitive compensation and comprehensive benefits. The salary range for this position in New York City is USD $80,000 to USD $90,000, depending on experience and qualifications. If hired in Ethiopia or India, the candidate will be hired via Vital Strategies office in those countries. The candidate must have authorization to work legally in the respective country at the time of hire.

Duties and Responsibilities

Data Integration and Analysis
• Develop tools to identify and inventory global and local health data systems as well as data sources across multiple sectors and ministries;
• Review and summarize models and options of existing effective integrated environment or health data systems for countries to consider;
• Work closely with epidemiologists and country teams to develop global and country-specific indicators and indices related to lead exposure risks;
• Provide technical support and guidance for the country team to access, align, and integrate health, environmental, social, economic, and demographic data from Ministries of Health, Ministries of the Environment, and other governmental and nongovernmental agencies;
• Develop a model metadata tool for national data systems;
• Support the design and maintenance of analytical datasets, reports, health panels, dashboards, and visualization tools (e.g., Power BI, Excel, R Markdown, or Tableau) for internal and external use;
• Define database structures, relationships, and workflows to ensure efficient integration, storage, and retrieval of blood lead level (BLL) and related epidemiological, demographic, and environmental data;
• Provide guidance to country teams to evaluate data quality, completeness, and consistency; perform data cleaning and validation;
• Collaborate with Ministries of Health, Ministries of the Environment, and other governmental and non‑governmental agencies to align architecture standards with existing health information systems and environmental systems (e.g., SINAN, SIASUS, SISOLO, SISAGUA).

Stakeholder Engagement
• Work in collaboration with other international NGOs that are part of the Lead Poisoning Prevention Initiative that work with institutions that may hold relevant data;
• Work with appropriate authorities and stakeholders across sectors to build and maintain awareness of broader lead‑related initiatives;
• Coordinate with all key stakeholders to ensure regular and timely communication and progress of program activities;
• Participate in technical discussions and working groups to contribute and inform program progress;
• Communicate results effectively to technical and non‑technical audiences, including health officials, laboratory teams, health workers, and policymakers.

Technical Support
• Provide analytical and methodological guidance to country teams related to data system development and maintenance;
• Assist in the formulation of national strategies and action plans on data integration;
• Support training sessions and workshops related to data integration and surveillance;
• Contribute to capacity strengthening efforts to enhance local analytical competencies.

Program Implementation and Coordination
• Collaborate with global teams to monitor and report the progress of the implementation of data integration;
• Support the planning and coordination of data collection, data flow, and information management processes;
• Contribute to the dissemination of findings through technical presentations, meetings, and publications;
• Ensure timely delivery of analytical outputs aligned with project milestones and government reporting needs;
• Assist with other duties assigned by the supervisor.

Qualifications

Education

Master s degree in computer science, data science, information technology, statistics, public health, or related field.

Skills and Abilities
• Proficiency in defining database structures, relational schemas, and workflows for complex multi‑sectoral datasets (health, environmental, demographic).
• Ability to align data architecture standards across disparate governmental information systems (e.g., SINAN, SIASUS).
• Strong quantitative and analytical skills with attention to detail and accuracy;
• Excellent communication and visualization skills to present complex data clearly;
• Ability to collaborate with epidemiologists to translate health risks (e.g., lead exposure) into measurable global and country‑specific indices.
• Ability to navigate relationships with diverse stakeholders, including Ministries of Health, Ministries of the Environment, NGOs, and laboratory teams.
• Ability to communicate analytical results to technical experts and non‑technical policymakers.
• Ability to provide analytical guidance to field teams regarding data system maintenance and strategy.
• Experience in facilitating training sessions and workshops to enhance local technical competencies.
• Skill in contributing to the formulation of national‑level action plans and implementation strategies for data integration.
• High level of initiative, organization, and problem‑solving ability;
• Professional proficiency in English (oral and written).
• Ability to work collaboratively in multidisciplinary and multi‑cultural teams and experience working in government environments is a plus;

Experience

Required
• Minimum 6 to 7 years of professional experience in computer science, data science, information technology, data analysis and/or health surveillance applied to public health or environmental health;
• Experience in managing and analyzing large data sets or health surveillance datasets;
• Experience working with government health or environmental departments;
• Experience in using software to warehouse data and create data visualization and dashboards (e.g., Microsoft Azure or Fabric, SQL‑Server, Power BI, Tableau, Shiny);
• Experience working with statistical software such as R, SAS, SPSS, Stata.

Preferred
• Experience working with global, regional, and large‑scale national;
• Health information systems (e.g., DHIS2) and with cross‑sectoral datasets;
• Experience in systematic toolkit development and capacity building;
• Familiarity with geospatial data and spatial analysis tools (QGIS, ArcGIS);
• Advanced proficiency in R, Python, and/or SQL;
• Experience in applying AI tools to quantitative data;
• Experience working in partnership with governmental institutions and international organizations

Working Conditions and Physical Requirements

This is a full‑time position based in our India office, following a hybrid schedule that requires four days per week in the office. The candidate must have authorization to work legally in India at the time of hire. The role includes regular collaboration with colleagues and stakeholders across different time zones and will require availability to travel internationally to attend meetings with partners or participate in field activities.

Additional Information

As a two‑time Great Place to Work certified organization, Vital Strategies India is proud to foster a culture rooted in respect, collaboration, integrity, and inclusion. We welcome applications from individuals of all backgrounds and do not discriminate on any basis protected by country or local laws.

We are committed to maintaining a professional environment where everyone is treated with dignity and where safeguarding is paramount we uphold zero tolerance for sexual harassment, exploitation, or abuse, and thoroughly vet all final candidates.

The salary range for this position is competitive, and complemented by a strong retirement plan, flexible basket reimbursement options, comprehensive healthcare coverage, and paid leave ensuring our people feel supported, valued, and empowered to thrive both professionally and personally.

1. POSITION VACANT: Senior Research Advisor - Data Science, Vital Strategies India Services Private Limited (VSISPL), New Delhi

2. ORGANISATIONAL AND PROJECT BACKGROUND:

Vital Strategies India Services Private Limited, with a registered office at New Delhi, is a social enterprise that provides technical and management consultancy services to address the leading causes of death, disease or injury and improve health outcomes. It seeks to provide innovative, cost-efficient solutions to global clients that are locally relevant, effective, and enduring by pursuing high-value partnerships and leveraging India's high-quality human capital and technology advantage.

All members of the Vital Strategies India team embody the organization's values and are integral to promoting our brand, supporting our growth, and ensuring operational excellence.

For more information about Vital Strategies, visit https://www.vitalstrategies.org/

3. JOB DESCRIPTION/ RESPONSIBILITIES:

Reporting to the Associate Director - Research, the Senior Research Advisor - Data Science (SRA-DS) based in New Delhi, will lead the design, management, and translation of advanced data science and digital intelligence initiatives within the Policy & Communication Division of Vital Strategies India Services Private Limited.

The Senior Research Advisor will work closely with program leads and external partners to oversee cross-country data engineering, AI-enabled analytics, and digital monitoring systems that inform policy. This role is responsible for leading applied analytics and machine learning-based classification, harmonizing multi-platform and multi-country datasets, developing decision-focused dashboards, and translating complex digital and social listening data into actionable insights for governments and partners.

The position is full-time and based in New Delhi, requiring a valid work permit for India, the ability to work across time zones, and periodic domestic or international travel as needed.

Key Responsibilities:

(A) Data Engineering, Harmonization & Governance:

(1) Design, implement, and maintain data pipelines for digital and social media data sources, ensuring clean, well-documented, and reproducible datasets;

(2) Align data structures, metadata standards, and coding frameworks (Python preferred) across multiple datasets to enable cross-country and longitudinal analyses;

(3) Support data governance, documentation, and quality assurance processes to ensure consistency, accuracy, and cross-country comparability of digital monitoring systems.

(B) Applied Analytics, Modeling & AI-Based Classification:

(1) Apply advanced data science, statistical, and machine learning methods, including classification, clustering, and text analysis, to generate policy-relevant insights;

(2) Train, test, and refine AI and Large Language Model (LLM)-based classification systems for digital content analysis, documenting methodological improvements and validation processes;

(3) Conduct complex quantitative and qualitative analyses, including statistical modeling, trend analysis, and mixed-methods synthesis.

(C) Digital Intelligence, Social Listening & Online Behavior Monitoring:

(1) Lead the analysis of digital content and digital media campaigns across global health communication programs, including social media platforms, online marketing content, and other publicly available digital signals;

(2) Support social listening and online behavior monitoring initiatives to assess narratives, exposure, engagement, and marketing tactics related to public health issues;

(3) Conduct trend analysis, content analysis, and comparative regional analyses to identify shifts in digital communication tactics, targeting strategies and online behavior over time.

(D) Visualization, Dashboards & Decision Support:

(1) Develop and maintain clear, decision-focused dashboards and visualizations (internal and external-facing) using tools such as Power BI;

(2) Ensure dashboards and analytical outputs are updated regularly, quality-checked, and tailored to the needs of internal teams, governments, and external partners;

(3) Troubleshoot data and visualization issues to ensure reliability and usability of outputs.

(E) Research Management:

(1) Lead cross-country research planning and contribute to applied research design including protocol development, analytical plans, and evaluation approaches as needed;

(2) Lead data science and analytics workstreams, ensuring methodological rigor, quality assurance, and delivery of policy-relevant insights aligned with project objectives, including oversight of data pipelines, analysis, and reporting;

(3) Coordinate and manage project implementation as required, monitoring technical milestones, timelines, and deliverables, and updating workplans to reflect analytic needs and operational realities;

(4) Manage vendor coordination, contracts, ethics processes, field monitoring, and related activities.

(F) Reporting, Knowledge Translation & External Engagement:

(1) Draft and contribute to high-quality reports, monthly briefs, desk research summaries, technical memos, policy briefs and academic manuscripts;

(2) Translate digital intelligence and analytical findings into actionable insights that inform campaigns, regulatory discussions, and policy design, working closely with communications and country teams;

(3) Serve as the primary technical liaison with partners and stakeholders, maintaining clear communication, facilitating structured input, and ensuring timely dissemination and access to data products, findings, and project outputs;

(4) Provide technical guidance and training to researchers, analysts, and program teams through training and knowledge-sharing on analytics, AI-based classification, and data visualization;

(5) Coordinate with external partners, including academic institutions, technology vendors, research agencies, and multilateral organizations to integrate research insights into programmatic and policy initiatives, build collaborative partnerships, and promote knowledge translation and adoption.

4. QUALIFICATIONS, EXPERIENCE AND COMPETENCIES:

Qualifications:

Master's degree in Public Health, Data Science, Statistics, Epidemiology, Computer Science, Behavioral/Social Sciences, Economics, or related field; Ph.D. preferred.

Experience:

(1) 10 years of progressive experience in applied research, data analytics, statistical modelling, or analytics roles relevant to public health, policy or strategic communications for policy or regulatory exposure;

(2) Strong proficiency in programming languages - Python and SQL, with experience managing, cleaning, and analyzing large or complex datasets and ensuring reproducibility and data quality;

(3) Experience applying advanced quantitative and qualitative analytical methods, including statistical modeling, classification, clustering, text analysis, or mixed-methods approaches:

(4) Demonstrated experience leading the application of computational and machine learning methods to quantitative, qualitative and mixed-methods research, including scaling, validating, and interpreting unstructured data to inform communication programs decision-making;

(5) Demonstrated experience working with digital, media, or online data, including social media, web-based content, or digital campaign data;

(6) Experience developing clear, decision-focused dashboards and visualizations using Power BI or similar tools for both technical and non-technical;

(7) Familiarity with data governance, documentation, and harmonization challenges in multi-country or multi-platform contexts.

(8) Proven ability to manage multiple workstreams, work across time zones, and deliver high-quality outputs on deadline;

(9) Strong written and verbal communication skills in English, with the ability to explain technical concepts to non-technical audiences.

Skills and Competencies:

(1) Strong command of statistical software (SPSS, Python, R, STATA, NVivo, Atlas.ti) and statistical learning;

(2) Experience with AI/Machine Learning/LLM classification models preferred;

(3) Proficiency in dashboarding tools (Power BI, Excel);

(4) Demonstrated ability to synthesize data succinctly and clearly;

(5) Strong writing, analytical, and problem-solving skills;

(6) Ability to work across time zones and manage multiple deadlines;

(7) High attention to detail, data accuracy, and methodological rigor.

Working Conditions:

(1) This is a full-time position based in our New Delhi office, where a hybrid, 4-day-per-week office schedule is in place;

(2) Work across different time zones;

(3) Possible domestic/ international travel for research coordination and dissemination.

5. COMPENSATION OFFERED:

The salary range for this position is INR 34,00,000 to INR 40,00,000, complemented by a strong retirement plan, flexible basket reimbursement options, comprehensive healthcare coverage, and paid leave - ensuring our people feel supported, valued, and empowered to thrive both professionally and personally.

6. LOCATION: New Delhi, India

7. REFERENCE: SRA-DS-VSISPL
